  <h3>The Omni Commons</h3>
  <p>A collectively run community center in Oakland, the Omni Commons is one of the few DIY spaces left after the mass-evictions following the Ghost Ship fire. It is a hub for activism throughout the East Bay, providing space and resources for over a dozen collectives organized  around food justice, hacking, feminist screenprinting and more, as well as meeting space and educational resources for the community at large. Recent events include: general assemblies for direct action planning, legal observer trainings, and fundraising for noDAPL.</p>

