  <h3>People’s Community Medics</h3>
  <p>A grassroots Oakland organization that provides emergency medical training to residents of underserved neighborhoods. The collective formed in response to the murder of Oscar Grant, who was refused medical assistance by the police for 20 minutes. Neighbors are trained to administer aid in situations of seizure, bleeding trauma, and other medical emergencies, while waiting for EMT services to arrive. The group was founded by black mothers, Sharena Thomas and Lesley Phillips, and is an all-volunteer collective of 10 members. All their trainings are free.</p>

